headline: How To Earn $500 A Month From Tyson Foods Stock Ahead Of Q2 Earnings
summary: Tyson Foods, Inc. (NYSE:TSN) will release its second-quarter financial results before the opening bell on Monday, May 5. Analysts expect the Springdale, Arkansas-based company to report quarterly earnings at 82 cents per share, up from 62 cents per share in the year-ago period. Tyson Foods projects quarterly revenue of $13.14 billion, compared to $13.07 billion a year earlier, according to data from Benzinga Pro.
